 WRAP AROUND v., WRAPAROUND n. 1. This is "jargon" in its normal computer
usage, i.e., describing the action of a counter that starts over at 0 or at
MINUS INFINITY after its maximum value has been reached, and continues
incrementing, either because it is programmed to do so, or because of an
overflow like a car's odometer starting over at 0. 2. To CHANGE PHASE
gradually and continuously by maintaining a steady wake-sleep cycle somewhat
longer than 24 hours, e.g. living 6 long days in a week.